data.title: Yo Quero Taco Bell
data.text: Home of the encherito  Quesarito and tacos too.  Breakfast lunch or dinner too, taco Bell has whats right for you.

data.title: Really convenient for a fast food pit stop
data.text:
Driving south on the Interstate late on Friday evening, we were both hungry and thirsty.
Turned off and found this Taco Bell easily and quite convenient.
Food was much as expected of a fast food - but the service was good and friendly and we were well satisfied with what we were served.
We left replete!

data.title: Friendly fast service but an inconvenient location
data.text: Decided to stop by on the way home for a quick and reliable burrito.    The service and burrito were as good or better than any Taco Bell.  However, getting to the restaurant parking lot was tough.   If you are on La Paz going from East to West you can turn  easily right into the parking lot.  If  your are continuing Westbound then you can make an easy right turn out of the parking lot onto  La Paz.   Any other combination of directions will cause you to drive at least 1/4 mile out of your way and around the entire strip center parking lot to get to Taco Bell.  That will be frustrating if you are hungry or in a hurry.
